				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Observation for acquiring Amy Whip<a name="23392"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 3:43 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Just to give you all some info..
<br />

<br />
Im a 65 bard and recently soloed fear for my amy whip. It was a pain in the a$, but here is my experience:
<br />

<br />
I zoned in with selo's up and inviso ready (many mobs there dont see inviso).. Fired up inviso and immediatly ran north and alittle west.
<br />

<br />
Once you reach the northwest corner you can use fade or log out. I strongly recommend you do NOT try and do this unless you have fade, as I dont see how you would survive and/or pull the temple without it.
<br />

<br />
I cleared the mobs out of the northwest corner of zone. There were no casters, by the time I was done I had kited around 15 mobs to their death that all aggroed me at some point.
<br />

<br />
One note about this, dont make my mistake and charm the mobs to attempt to kill them faster. You could do this successfully but only AFTER you kite all the imps to death. If you do not, they will send your charmed mob (or if you charm them, the mobs they are attacking) randomly near you around the zone, often aggroing even more mobs.
<br />

<br />
I would suspect if I had not done this I would have only needed to clear about 5-8 mobs at the most.
<br />

<br />
Once NW zone is clear, you are ready to pull from temple once you have mana to fade.  I hit selos and ran north of the temple. Then I simply ran across the fire to the north part of the temple, ran up to the top, and sat there for a second until I got aggro from inside the temple (something will attempt to dispel you usually). Fire back up selo's and run out. Run back toward the NW corner, but not too far, and turn around and watch the temple for mobs coming. If you do this, then sometimes you will only get a handful (like 1-3) mobs that come out and you dont need to waste fade mana.  This worked the first 3-4 pulls. The next pull I tried in this way the entire temple came out, so I had to fade and lull some and pick a few out of the herd.
<br />

<br />
The tentacle terrors are not dangerous to kite, so dont fear them.  However, the Glare Lords can be because I think they can root, they seemed like wizards. Also I wouldn't try to kite around more than one Amy Knight at once. They are SKs and I was quite afraid of them landing darkness on me at one point b/c I resisted a cast from one of them. I immediatly faded and let the knight leave and picked out the 2 warriors I was kiting with him.
<br />

<br />
I got my amy whip this way my first attempt at doing it, after killing about 5 warriors or so.
<br />

<br />
Remember, fade is a must.</span></td>
